WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:22.760 align:middle line:90%


00:00:22.760 --> 00:00:25.595 align:middle line:84%
>>The point of all of the great
spiritual teachings is

00:00:25.595 --> 00:00:28.980 align:middle line:84%
that you can step into infinity
today, reside in

00:00:28.980 --> 00:00:33.410 align:middle line:84%
infinity consciously, and
source from there.

00:00:33.410 --> 00:00:37.290 align:middle line:84%
Within infinity, you will become
the architect and the

00:00:37.290 --> 00:00:41.140 align:middle line:84%
dreamer of the great matrix of
expression and creation.

00:00:41.140 --> 00:00:45.320 align:middle line:84%
If you don't do that, then you
are caught in someone else's

00:00:45.320 --> 00:00:48.100 align:middle line:84%
dream and someone else's
nightmare.

00:00:48.100 --> 00:00:51.430 align:middle line:84%
The practice of infinity is
really about dreaming your

00:00:51.430 --> 00:00:52.834 align:middle line:90%
world into being.

00:00:52.834 --> 00:01:24.970 align:middle line:90%


00:01:24.970 --> 00:01:28.220 align:middle line:84%
>>People have to understand
that there is no death.

00:01:28.220 --> 00:01:32.620 align:middle line:84%
A person like me, who's been
dead, has no choice but to see

00:01:32.620 --> 00:01:33.850 align:middle line:90%
it this way.

00:01:33.850 --> 00:01:35.730 align:middle line:84%
The end of something is
just the beginning

00:01:35.730 --> 00:01:37.250 align:middle line:90%
of something else.

00:01:37.250 --> 00:01:38.650 align:middle line:90%
There is no finite.

00:01:38.650 --> 00:01:43.510 align:middle line:84%
And once you see yourself as a
spiritual being, forget it.

00:01:43.510 --> 00:01:47.280 align:middle line:84%
A near death experience or any
thought of it is completely

00:01:47.280 --> 00:01:51.520 align:middle line:84%
impossible and totally out
of my framework in 1975.

00:01:51.520 --> 00:01:52.890 align:middle line:90%
I wouldn't have believed it.

00:01:52.890 --> 00:01:55.760 align:middle line:84%
You couldn't have gotten me to
believe it, except I was

00:01:55.760 --> 00:01:58.780 align:middle line:84%
talking on the telephone on
a Wednesday afternoon.

00:01:58.780 --> 00:02:02.185 align:middle line:84%
Lightning hit the phone line and
came down, and it hit me

00:02:02.185 --> 00:02:03.840 align:middle line:90%
in the side of my head.

00:02:03.840 --> 00:02:07.450 align:middle line:84%
It went down my spine and it
welded the nails of the heels

00:02:07.450 --> 00:02:11.180 align:middle line:84%
of my shoes to the nails in the
floor, which grounded me,

00:02:11.180 --> 00:02:14.460 align:middle line:84%
threw me in the air, suspended
me in the air and slammed me

00:02:14.460 --> 00:02:16.270 align:middle line:90%
down on the bed.

00:02:16.270 --> 00:02:19.710 align:middle line:84%
I was dead for 28 minutes,
completely paralyzed for six

00:02:19.710 --> 00:02:22.530 align:middle line:84%
days, partially paralyzed
for seven months.

00:02:22.530 --> 00:02:26.770 align:middle line:84%
It took me two years to learn
to walk and feed myself.

00:02:26.770 --> 00:02:30.955 align:middle line:84%
>>I was born 1924 in a little
town called Breig.

00:02:30.955 --> 00:02:35.800 align:middle line:84%
My grandfather owned two large
textile mills, the length of a

00:02:35.800 --> 00:02:37.390 align:middle line:90%
whole street.

00:02:37.390 --> 00:02:43.080 align:middle line:84%
And the whole town worked
for them, weaving.

00:02:43.080 --> 00:02:45.490 align:middle line:84%
There were two brothers,
Otto and Fritz.

00:02:45.490 --> 00:02:48.070 align:middle line:84%
Fritz was my uncle and Otto
my father, and they

00:02:48.070 --> 00:02:49.830 align:middle line:90%
each ran one mill--

00:02:49.830 --> 00:02:52.020 align:middle line:84%
one in Freistadt and
one in Breig.

00:02:52.020 --> 00:02:53.860 align:middle line:90%
And we were very rich.

00:02:53.860 --> 00:02:56.930 align:middle line:84%
And then came the
Nazis, age 33.

00:02:56.930 --> 00:03:00.055 align:middle line:84%
And the very first thing they
did was shoot my father on New

00:03:00.055 --> 00:03:02.160 align:middle line:90%
Year's Eve through the window.

00:03:02.160 --> 00:03:08.020 align:middle line:84%
>>I was lying down on my
bed one night around

00:03:08.020 --> 00:03:11.580 align:middle line:90%
15 or 18 years ago.

00:03:11.580 --> 00:03:15.630 align:middle line:84%
I had just had a terrific
argument with my then wife,

00:03:15.630 --> 00:03:16.420 align:middle line:90%
God rest her soul.

00:03:16.420 --> 00:03:20.990 align:middle line:84%
She's celebrated her
continuation day.

00:03:20.990 --> 00:03:25.240 align:middle line:84%
And we had had some kind of a
spat about nothing, really.

00:03:25.240 --> 00:03:27.320 align:middle line:90%
Most spats are about nothing--

00:03:27.320 --> 00:03:30.690 align:middle line:84%
whose turn was it to take out
the trash or whatever.

00:03:30.690 --> 00:03:35.900 align:middle line:90%
But I was in a mood of upset.

00:03:35.900 --> 00:03:37.010 align:middle line:90%
So I was lying on my bed.

00:03:37.010 --> 00:03:38.462 align:middle line:90%
I had gone to bed quite early.

00:03:38.462 --> 00:03:40.540 align:middle line:84%
I just slammed the door
to the bedroom.

00:03:40.540 --> 00:03:43.330 align:middle line:84%
I was there just to get
away from it all.

00:03:43.330 --> 00:03:46.156 align:middle line:84%
And as I got into the bedroom,
I realized what am

00:03:46.156 --> 00:03:46.800 align:middle line:90%
I going to do here?

00:03:46.800 --> 00:03:48.160 align:middle line:90%
It's 7:45 at night.

00:03:48.160 --> 00:03:50.130 align:middle line:90%
I'm not ready to go to sleep.

00:03:50.130 --> 00:03:52.460 align:middle line:84%
I had no television in the
bedroom, and as it happened,

00:03:52.460 --> 00:03:54.605 align:middle line:84%
no reading material
on that occasion.

00:03:54.605 --> 00:03:57.020 align:middle line:90%
And I thought, wow, boy.

00:03:57.020 --> 00:03:57.250 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:03:57.250 --> 00:04:00.846 align:middle line:84%
Well, I'll just try
to go to sleep.

00:04:00.846 --> 00:04:05.170 align:middle line:84%
So I turned the lights out
and I lie there in the

00:04:05.170 --> 00:04:08.410 align:middle line:84%
semi-darkness of
a 7:45 evening.

00:04:08.410 --> 00:04:11.910 align:middle line:84%
And then I allowed myself to
just let go of everything,

00:04:11.910 --> 00:04:15.290 align:middle line:84%
because I remember thinking,
why can't

00:04:15.290 --> 00:04:17.835 align:middle line:90%
people just get along?

00:04:17.835 --> 00:04:21.070 align:middle line:90%
Why is it so hard?

00:04:21.070 --> 00:04:25.480 align:middle line:84%
I see now why nations can't
get along with nations and

00:04:25.480 --> 00:04:27.625 align:middle line:84%
civilizations with civilizations
and cultures

00:04:27.625 --> 00:04:28.260 align:middle line:90%
with cultures.

00:04:28.260 --> 00:04:32.115 align:middle line:84%
I can't even get along with my
own wife, who I love dearly.

00:04:32.115 --> 00:04:37.750 align:middle line:84%
What does it take just
to simply get along?

00:04:37.750 --> 00:04:41.358 align:middle line:84%
And I remember feeling
so sad about that.

00:04:41.358 --> 00:04:44.700 align:middle line:84%
>>The first time that
I died, I was six.

00:04:44.700 --> 00:04:48.900 align:middle line:84%
I became very ill and needed
massive blood transfusions.

00:04:48.900 --> 00:04:50.970 align:middle line:84%
And I have a very rare blood
type, B negative.

00:04:50.970 --> 00:04:53.120 align:middle line:90%
And we could not find donors.

00:04:53.120 --> 00:04:56.630 align:middle line:84%
And I spent a week in a coma
while they found donors with

00:04:56.630 --> 00:04:59.040 align:middle line:90%
my blood type.

00:04:59.040 --> 00:05:02.270 align:middle line:84%
My body was being wracked
by fever.

00:05:02.270 --> 00:05:05.280 align:middle line:84%
And it was extremely painful
to be inside my body.

00:05:05.280 --> 00:05:09.130 align:middle line:84%
And I remember lifting up from
my body and going to the

00:05:09.130 --> 00:05:12.340 align:middle line:84%
corner of the room and hovering
in the corner of the

00:05:12.340 --> 00:05:15.740 align:middle line:84%
room, shivering and saying,
who is that little boy?

00:05:15.740 --> 00:05:17.690 align:middle line:90%
And why is he so sad?

00:05:17.690 --> 00:05:19.250 align:middle line:90%
Why is he crying?

00:05:19.250 --> 00:05:22.430 align:middle line:84%
Why is he not be able to open
his eyes, and going back to

00:05:22.430 --> 00:05:25.420 align:middle line:84%
the lying down next to him
and feeling the pain.

00:05:25.420 --> 00:05:27.860 align:middle line:84%
The closer I got to that little
body, the more pain I

00:05:27.860 --> 00:05:28.950 align:middle line:90%
could feel.

00:05:28.950 --> 00:05:31.470 align:middle line:84%
And I would withdraw to the
corner of the room.

00:05:31.470 --> 00:05:35.570 align:middle line:84%
>>But what happened was at the
point where I could no longer

00:05:35.570 --> 00:05:39.021 align:middle line:84%
sustain the burning of my body--
my eyes hurt, and it

00:05:39.021 --> 00:05:41.950 align:middle line:84%
was like I had consumed battery
acid and I'm burning

00:05:41.950 --> 00:05:45.545 align:middle line:84%
and I'm on fire-- then I
lift out of my body.

00:05:45.545 --> 00:05:47.453 align:middle line:84%
And I'm in this blue-grey
place.

00:05:47.453 --> 00:05:49.000 align:middle line:90%
I didn't care where it was.

00:05:49.000 --> 00:05:51.690 align:middle line:84%
It was better than where
I just left.

00:05:51.690 --> 00:05:52.870 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:05:52.870 --> 00:05:55.920 align:middle line:84%
And I could feel this sense of
comfort and sense of safety.

00:05:55.920 --> 00:05:59.830 align:middle line:90%


00:05:59.830 --> 00:06:04.220 align:middle line:84%
Then I had this point of where
I was listening to these

00:06:04.220 --> 00:06:05.470 align:middle line:90%
chimes and this music.

00:06:05.470 --> 00:06:07.920 align:middle line:90%


00:06:07.920 --> 00:06:10.970 align:middle line:84%
And then all of a sudden, this
blue grey place became a

00:06:10.970 --> 00:06:12.290 align:middle line:90%
tunnel of light.

00:06:12.290 --> 00:06:14.165 align:middle line:84%
And I moved down this tunnel,
and I came into

00:06:14.165 --> 00:06:15.200 align:middle line:90%
this place of light.

00:06:15.200 --> 00:06:19.480 align:middle line:84%
And I was watching what was
going on around me.

00:06:19.480 --> 00:06:26.190 align:middle line:84%
And the sensations and the
beauty of this place totally

00:06:26.190 --> 00:06:28.800 align:middle line:84%
distracted me from the world
I had just left.

00:06:28.800 --> 00:06:32.870 align:middle line:90%


00:06:32.870 --> 00:06:36.670 align:middle line:84%
So I'd have to say that some
people are enlightened.

00:06:36.670 --> 00:06:37.920 align:middle line:90%
I was in lightning.

00:06:37.920 --> 00:06:42.440 align:middle line:90%


00:06:42.440 --> 00:06:44.700 align:middle line:84%
>>And suddenly, I
was accompanied

00:06:44.700 --> 00:06:47.580 align:middle line:90%
by beings, by angels.

00:06:47.580 --> 00:06:49.650 align:middle line:84%
I call them angels because
they were luminous.

00:06:49.650 --> 00:06:52.660 align:middle line:84%
They were translucent
white that held me.

00:06:52.660 --> 00:06:54.240 align:middle line:90%
And I asked them, who are you?

00:06:54.240 --> 00:06:55.640 align:middle line:90%
I was scared at the beginning.

00:06:55.640 --> 00:06:58.470 align:middle line:84%
And they said, we are
your parents.

00:06:58.470 --> 00:07:01.780 align:middle line:84%
We are your real parents,
your true parents.

00:07:01.780 --> 00:07:04.570 align:middle line:84%
And who is that little
boy, I asked.

00:07:04.570 --> 00:07:06.080 align:middle line:90%
They said, that's you.

00:07:06.080 --> 00:07:09.520 align:middle line:84%
But that's not always
been you.

00:07:09.520 --> 00:07:11.100 align:middle line:84%
>>Nazism now was
in full bloom.

00:07:11.100 --> 00:07:15.290 align:middle line:90%
It was '34.

00:07:15.290 --> 00:07:20.370 align:middle line:84%
And then it was '35, 1935,
and it was the many, many

00:07:20.370 --> 00:07:22.000 align:middle line:90%
restrictions against the Jews.

00:07:22.000 --> 00:07:24.360 align:middle line:84%
It got worse and worse
and worse.

00:07:24.360 --> 00:07:29.310 align:middle line:84%
The end, they came and they
loaded up 35 old ladies and a

00:07:29.310 --> 00:07:32.880 align:middle line:84%
