took them to Auschwitz.

00:07:32.880 --> 00:07:37.670 align:middle line:84%
Before that, my mother heard
that there was such a thing as

00:07:37.670 --> 00:07:40.660 align:middle line:84%
a children's transport,
the Kindertransport.

00:07:40.660 --> 00:07:44.530 align:middle line:84%
They rescued 5,000
Jewish children.

00:07:44.530 --> 00:07:46.290 align:middle line:90%
They took some to Holland.

00:07:46.290 --> 00:07:47.500 align:middle line:90%
They didn't survive.

00:07:47.500 --> 00:07:50.370 align:middle line:84%
And the ones that were in the
back of the train they took to

00:07:50.370 --> 00:07:53.220 align:middle line:84%
England, and because we
were late, we were in

00:07:53.220 --> 00:07:54.550 align:middle line:90%
the back of the train.

00:07:54.550 --> 00:07:55.650 align:middle line:90%
And that's how I'm here.

00:07:55.650 --> 00:07:58.240 align:middle line:90%
This is why I'm still alive.

00:07:58.240 --> 00:08:04.020 align:middle line:84%
>>So I lied there in the bed,
and I just sunk back into

00:08:04.020 --> 00:08:08.320 align:middle line:84%
